<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,291,678]" pageId="2" pageNumber="436">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,615,642]" pageId="2" pageNumber="436">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Cai &amp; He" authorityName="Cai &amp; He" authorityYear="1997" box="[575,779,616,643]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Eleazara" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="436" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yangi">
<emphasis box="[575,664,617,642]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="436">E. yangi</emphasis>
Cai &amp; He
</taxonomicName>
but differs in having a testaceous body and scutellum length shorter than head length.
</paragraph>
